## 2. Principios e Tecnicas
- To the BPB team, thank you for your patience, encouragement, and faith through long evenings and weekend revisions.
- To the readers, thank you for your time.
- I hope this book helps you understand use cases and real-world applications of AI in healthcare.
- Data Science for Healthcare About the Author Nitin Singh is a data science professional with over 14 years of experience working at the intersection of healthcare, analytics, and artificial intelligence.
- His career began with data-driven problem solving at global organizations such as Amazon and Deloitte, where he built a strong grounding in large-scale data systems and business analytics.
- Over time, his focus shifted towards using data to improve healthcare delivery and decision-making.
- At Primera Medical Technologies, a captive unit of Prime Healthcare in the United States, Nitin led projects on predictive modeling and natural language processing aimed at enhancing hospital operations and patient outcomes.
- Later, as part of the real-world evidence team at Sanofi, he worked on machine learning and generative AI applications that connected pharmaceutical insights with real-world clinical practice.
- Academically, Nitin has an engineering background and is an alumnus of the Indian School of Business, where he completed the advanced management program in business analytics.
- He is currently pursuing a PhD at the Indian Institute of Technology, Patna in the field of artificial intelligence and data science.

## 3. Aplicacoes Praticas
- His work reflects a deep belief that data science achieves its highest value when used with empathy and purpose.
- Through his research and writing, he continues to explore how data and technology can make healthcare more efficient, equitable, and human-centered.
- Data Science for Healthcare About the Reviewers Sreenivasareddy is an experienced lead data and analytics engineer with a strong track record of delivering scalable, high-performance data solutions across healthcare, finance, insurance, and supply chain domains.
- Currently focused on designing and modernizing data platforms using cloud-native technologies and tools, including Azure, Snowflake, and Databricks.
- With deep expertise in data engineering, ETL/ELT pipelines, BI dashboards, and analytics modernization, he has a passion for building efficient, automated, and production-ready data workflows that drive actionable insights.
- Committed to data quality, performance, and observability, ensuring the correct data reaches the right users at the right time.
- He is an active reader of comics, nonfiction, and IT-related books, and serves as a technical reviewer for various books on data engineering, data science, and business intelligence.
- Sujan is a data enthusiast with experience working in diverse domains such as healthcare manufacturing, digital accessibility, and enterprise AI.
- Passionate about applying AI/ ML use cases in varied setup.
- Curious to explore new tools, techniques and data sources which in turn adds value to business by building workflows, model training, and curating use cases.

## 4. Topicos Avancados
- Experience working with finance and supply chain domains as part of enterprise AI.
- Always up for new challenges and applying optimized solutions in scale.
- Kevin Joseph K is a tech enthusiast, author, and tutor with expertise in AI, machine learning, and generative AI.
- He has authored two books and published a research paper on operating systems.
- Alongside academic and industry experience, he has worked on data-driven solutions in the healthcare sector, focusing on automation and real-world impact.
- Outside of technology, he enjoys reading and expresses his creativity through playing the piano.
- Data Science for Healthcare C HAPTER 1 Introduction to Data Science in Healthcare Introduction In the nexus of healthcare and technology, data science emerges as a transformative force.
- This chapter introduces the foundational principles that bridge healthcare and data science, offering readers an insight into the potential of data to reshape patient care, research, and administration.
- We will explore key data sources in healthcare, from electronic health records ( EHRs ) to wearable tech, and touch upon the tools and techniques that turn this data into actionable insights.
- By the end of this chapter, readers will have a solid understanding of the essential role data science plays in modern healthcare.
